## Authoring Slides

- [Markup]({{ site.url }}/markup/): Structure slides directly in HTML, including nested and grouped slides.
- [Markdown]({{ site.url }}/markdown/): Author slides in Markdown, including external Markdown files.
- [Layout]({{ site.url }}/layout/): Arrange slide content with helpers for positioning, sizing, and alignment.
- [Backgrounds]({{ site.url }}/backgrounds/): Configure slide backgrounds with colors, images, video, and gradients.
- [Media]({{ site.url }}/media/): Embed iframes, video, audio, and other rich media in presentations.
- [Lightbox]({{ site.url }}/lightbox/): Open images, videos, or linked resources in a presentation lightbox.
- [Presenting Code]({{ site.url }}/code/): Add syntax-highlighted code, line highlighting, and code presentation patterns.
- [Math]({{ site.url }}/math/): Render LaTeX and mathematical notation in slides.
- [Fragments]({{ site.url }}/fragments/): Reveal slide content incrementally in ordered steps.
- [Links]({{ site.url }}/links/): Use links and link previews inside presentations.
- [Slide Visibility]({{ site.url }}/slide-visibility/): Control whether slides are visible, hidden, or excluded from navigation.

## Customization

- [Themes]({{ site.url }}/themes/): Apply, customize, and create reveal.js themes.
- [Transitions]({{ site.url }}/transitions/): Configure slide and background transitions.
- [Configuration Options]({{ site.url }}/config/): Full configuration reference for reveal.js initialization and runtime behavior.
- [Presentation Size]({{ site.url }}/presentation-size/): Configure deck dimensions, scaling, and responsive sizing behavior.

## Presentation Features

- [Vertical Slides]({{ site.url }}/vertical-slides/): Create vertical stacks of slides inside a horizontal deck.
- [Auto-Animate]({{ site.url }}/auto-animate/): Animate matching elements automatically between consecutive slides.
- [Auto-Slide]({{ site.url }}/auto-slide/): Advance slides automatically on a timer.
- [Speaker View]({{ site.url }}/speaker-view/): Use speaker notes and presenter controls in a separate window.
- [Scroll View]({{ site.url }}/scroll-view/): Present decks as scrollable documents instead of paged slides.
- [Slide Numbers]({{ site.url }}/slide-numbers/): Display and format current slide numbers.
- [Jump to Slide]({{ site.url }}/jump-to-slide/): Navigate directly to a slide using keyboard shortcuts.
- [Touch Navigation]({{ site.url }}/touch-navigation/): Control presentations with touch and swipe gestures.
- [PDF Export]({{ site.url }}/pdf-export/): Print or export presentations to PDF.
- [Overview Mode]({{ site.url }}/overview/): Zoom out to see all slides in a deck overview.
- [Fullscreen]({{ site.url }}/fullscreen/): Present and control decks in fullscreen mode.

